00:51:39,544 --> 00:51:41,424
When a dog barks...

743
00:51:41,524 --> 00:51:44,274
all the other dogs start barking
without knowing the reason.

744
00:51:47,074 --> 00:51:49,224
Now that I see it, I understand.

745
00:51:50,124 --> 00:51:52,208
I was the dog in the neighborhood.

746
00:52:04,734 --> 00:52:08,294
Chief is not in her right mind.
How is it Ahn Chan-soo's fault?

747
00:52:08,394 --> 00:52:10,014
How could she conclude it so easily?

748
00:52:10,114 --> 00:52:11,896
-Does this make sense?
-It doesn't.

749
00:52:57,114 --> 00:52:58,084
Chief.

750
00:52:58,194 --> 00:53:01,654
This exclusive makes no sense.
How could this be Ahn Chan-soo’s fault?

751
00:53:03,784 --> 00:53:05,541
He's your friend, right?

752
00:53:07,354 --> 00:53:09,554
You're being irrational
because he’s your friend

753
00:53:09,654 --> 00:53:13,607
and I don’t intend to respond to
every little thing that has no logic.

754
00:53:15,107 --> 00:53:19,574
I'm not his friend
and I didn’t lose my rationality.

755
00:53:19,684 --> 00:53:21,074
Would you respond to me then?

756
00:53:22,236 --> 00:53:26,474
The report that policeman received was
an explosion of a household butane gas.

757
00:53:26,887 --> 00:53:28,529
It has nothing to do with this case.

758
00:53:28,974 --> 00:53:31,440
Of course he will say that
it’s got nothing to do with the case.

759
00:53:31,540 --> 00:53:32,800
Would he say it's his fault?

760
00:53:32,890 --> 00:53:35,330
Did you meet with the employee
who reported the explosion?

761
00:53:36,577 --> 00:53:39,030
I was going to, but he was unconscious.

762
00:53:39,460 --> 00:53:42,370
-It was so sad.
-It means that you didn’t meet him.

763
00:53:42,480 --> 00:53:46,919
Then what proof are you saying that
Ahn is responsible for this incident?

764
00:53:47,019 --> 00:53:48,502
Let me ask you.

765
00:53:49,339 --> 00:53:52,479
What proof do you have that Ahn
is not responsible?

766
00:53:53,017 --> 00:53:56,667
I have the CCTV footage as my evidence.
But what’s your evidence?

767
00:53:58,827 --> 00:54:01,408
And I just posed the suspicion.
I didn’t conclude it.

768
00:54:01,508 --> 00:54:03,861
-How is that a problem?
-It is a problem.

769
00:54:03,961 --> 00:54:06,391
People will accept that as truth.

770
00:54:06,481 --> 00:54:07,885
Just like 13 years ago.

771
00:54:13,101 --> 00:54:16,787
Why are you bringing up
what happened 13 years ago here?

772
00:54:16,887 --> 00:54:21,351
You also used shallow evidence that time
and destroyed a family.

773
00:54:21,491 --> 00:54:24,370
Then bring me at least
one shallow evidence and argue!

774
00:54:25,591 --> 00:54:27,821
Don’t shelter one sidedly
just because he’s your friend.

775
00:54:27,921 --> 00:54:30,921
Bring proper evidence as a reporter
and pose a suspicion.

776
00:54:34,081 --> 00:54:35,703
I’ll bring the evidence and come back.

777
00:54:41,261 --> 00:54:44,031
I’ll find the evidence that
Ahn Chan-soo is not responsible.

778
00:54:44,131 --> 00:54:48,766
I will not lose someone powerlessly
like 13 years ago.

779
00:54:53,101 --> 00:54:55,098
I will turn the flow
that you’re trying to change...

780
00:54:56,001 --> 00:54:58,038
back to where it should no matter what.

781
00:55:31,461 --> 00:55:35,894
-What brings you here?
-I’ll get right to the point.

782
00:55:36,191 --> 00:55:39,761
-My son likes your daughter.
-Excuse me?

783
00:55:40,691 --> 00:55:43,251
-My In-ha?
-Yes.

784
00:55:43,511 --> 00:55:47,031
-Didn’t you know?
-No, I didn't know.

785
00:55:47,131 --> 00:55:51,731
But I will make sure to control her.
I’ll tell her not to go near your son.

786
00:55:51,841 --> 00:55:55,051
-You can’t do that.
-Excuse me?

787
00:55:55,151 --> 00:55:59,191
I came to ask you
to look favorably on my son.

788
00:55:59,920 --> 00:56:03,321
-What did you say?
-Please help him.

789
00:56:03,421 --> 00:56:06,291
Please cheer on my son.

790
00:56:08,941 --> 00:56:12,584
What in the world?
The Chairwoman's son as a son-in-law...

791
00:56:14,960 --> 00:56:17,152
My fate is finally turning out well.

792
00:56:17,771 --> 00:56:19,146
My goodness.

793
00:56:23,921 --> 00:56:25,291
I don't want to.

794
00:56:25,391 --> 00:56:29,777
Why not? You might find your real family
if you go on TV.

795
00:56:30,381 --> 00:56:31,687
I don't want to find them!

796
00:56:32,451 --> 00:56:33,523
Dal-Po.

797
00:56:38,295 --> 00:56:40,090
I don't want to find them.

798
00:56:40,921 --> 00:56:42,578
So please...

799
00:56:43,621 --> 00:56:45,250
Please, mister.

800
00:56:45,658 --> 00:56:48,376
You... You remember your family,
don’t you?

801
00:56:49,891 --> 00:56:50,763
Don't you?

802
00:56:52,791 --> 00:56:54,567
Tell me what kind of people they were.

803
00:56:57,021 --> 00:56:59,146
Did they commit great sins or something?

804
00:57:00,461 --> 00:57:01,781
Is that why you're in hiding?

805
00:57:12,261 --> 00:57:15,763
Ohgwang and Godori and one two three...

806
00:57:16,861 --> 00:57:20,964
Three go, Kwangbak and Pibak
so you owe me 8 dollars and 40 cents.

807
00:57:23,531 --> 00:57:25,741
What if...

808
00:57:25,841 --> 00:57:29,781
some rich guy likes In-ha?
What do I do then?

809
00:57:29,881 --> 00:57:32,261
If he has a lot of money, that’s great.

810
00:57:32,361 --> 00:57:36,124
But does In-ha like him?

811
00:57:37,091 --> 00:57:39,131
What if...

812
00:57:39,231 --> 00:57:42,324
In-ha likes someone who has nothing?

813
00:57:42,424 --> 00:57:43,424
Really?

814
00:57:43,524 --> 00:57:49,827
-Then you should just...
-No, you can't be hasty!

815
00:57:50,037 --> 00:57:52,355
He's awfully rich.

816
00:57:52,455 --> 00:57:55,439
He’s like someone who has Ohgwang,
Mungta and has Godori.

817
00:57:55,579 --> 00:57:59,606
The other guy is has like Gwangbak, Pibak
and even Gaepae.

818
00:57:59,706 --> 00:58:01,936
-There’s that much difference?
-Yes.

819
00:58:02,036 --> 00:58:04,474
They are so far apart from each other.

820
00:58:06,966 --> 00:58:09,517
-Then you should have that poor guy...
-Father!

821
00:58:09,617 --> 00:58:12,539
You said In-ha likes this guy?

822
00:58:13,807 --> 00:58:18,662
Hey, you’re not a small minded guy
who would sell off your child.

823
00:58:18,762 --> 00:58:20,702
I am a small minded guy.

824
00:58:20,802 --> 00:58:23,566
It’s not even as big
as a small soy sauce dish.

825
00:58:27,676 --> 00:58:31,142
You shouldn’t compare like that.

826
00:58:32,824 --> 00:58:36,682
If you start to compare,
your happiness is finished...

827
00:58:37,215 --> 00:58:38,490
...and your unhappiness will begin.

828
00:58:38,580 --> 00:58:39,700
In-ha.

829
00:58:40,910 --> 00:58:42,984
I can’t hold on to you right now.

830
00:58:44,630 --> 00:58:46,180
But...

831
00:58:46,289 --> 00:58:48,119
Don’t go toward someone else.

832
00:58:55,346 --> 00:58:57,338
Okay. I won't.
